{"word":"H1902 - הִגָּיֹון - higgâyôwn - hig-gaw-yone' - Device","slug":"H1902","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">הִגָּיֹון</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>higgâyôwn"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>hig-gaw-yone'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Device"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D4;&#x05D2;&#x05BC;&#x05D9;&#x05D5;&#x05DF; - higga&#x0302;yo&#x0302;n</b> - <i>hig-gaw-yone'</i><p/>Intensive from <a href=\"#/H1897\">H1897</a>; a <i>murmuring</i> sound, that is, a musical notation (probably similar to the moder <i>affettuoso</i> to indicate solemnity of movement); by implication a <i>machination: - </i>device, Higgaion, meditation, solemn sound."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H1897\">H1897</a>, <a href=\"#/H1899\">H1899</a>, <a href=\"#/H1900\">H1900</a>"}]}